            "id": "bb3339e5fd304f74868ee",
            "questionText": "In a marine research submarine, an optical fibre has a core with a refractive index of $!$1.60$!$, and the critical angle for total internal reflection at the interface between the core and the cladding is $!$60^\\circ$!$. Assuming the speed of light in air is $!$3.0 \\times 10^8 \\text{ m/s}$!$, calculate the speed of light in the cladding.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "9281da211baf41499bd13",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct relation between the critical angle and the refractive indices of the core and cladding. Which formula best represents this relation?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "12c39f67-6487-45a1-ad1c-9b2d008d49da"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\sin c = \\frac{n_{cladding}}{n_{core}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\sin c = \\frac{n_{core}}{n_{cladding}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\sin c = n_{cladding} \\cdot n_{core}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "b3b2b717039e4b28a5cff",
                    "stepText": "Now, using the relation and the given values $!$n_{core} = 1.60$!$ and $!$c = 60^\\circ$!$, calculate the refractive index of the cladding. (Remember that you will need to compute $!$\\sin60^\\circ$!$ as part of this step.)",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "1.386"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "12c39f67-6487-45a1-ad1c-9b2d008d49da"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "0c6393b61778491eb491a",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that you have the refractive index of the cladding, identify the proper formula that relates the refractive index of a medium to the speed of light in air and the speed of light in that medium.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "0fd432f9-88af-4d36-8e87-5eae4916e921"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$n = \\frac{\\text{speed of light in air}}{\\text{speed of light in medium}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$n = \\frac{\\text{speed of light in medium}}{\\text{speed of light in air}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$n = \\text{speed of light in air} \\times \\text{speed of light in medium}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "e3acf11290ea406bb2e6d",
                    "stepText": "Finally, using the formula selected and the calculated refractive index for the cladding, compute the speed of light in the cladding. Substitute the given speed of light in air $!$3.0 \\times 10^8 \\text{ m/s}$!$ and the refractive index you found earlier.",
