            "id": "0fb84c9f197c480983e4f",
            "questionText": "A physics classroom uses a converging lens as a magnifying glass. A non-luminous pencil is placed at a certain distance from the optical center such that the resulting virtual image is $!$4$!$ times larger than the object. The lens has a power of $!$25 \\text{ D}$!$, and the magnifying glass follows the formula $!$\\frac{1}{f} = \\frac{1}{u} - \\frac{1}{v}$!$, where $!$u$!$ is the object distance, $!$v$!$ is the image distance, and $!$f$!$ is the focal length of the lens. Given this information, determine the distance at which the pencil was placed from the lens.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "b17a2dad79344f5da1ab6",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the type of lens and its usage in this scenario. Which option best describes the lens used when it functions as a magnifying glass?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
